 Kelley. Mr.  Kelley is in training for the Boston Marathon -- his 60th Boston Marathon. In 1928, when he was 21, he entered his first Boston Marathon but didn't finish. He dropped out three-quarters of the way through the race. The winners get a medal and $55000, says Mr. His best time ever was in 1945: 2 hours, 30 minutes, 40 seconds.  Kelley is to be the oldest competitor in the race this year -- as he has been for 15 years.  Kelley always trains at 5 a.  Kelley holds the endurance record for his age group. Unlike many runners, Mr. 